"Laurent" == Laurent Bossavit <morendil@micronet.fr> writes:

Laurent> "Orders which are not pursuant to an agreement between
Laurent> Players, or specifically permitted by the Rules, are be
Laurent> presumptively invalid", maybe ?

On consideration, I think it would be better to simply make it
improper to issue a Private Order except when permitted by the Rules
or by an agreement between Players (and restrict the latter case to
allowing such Orders to be directly only to Players who are party to
the agreement).  Such orders will be probatively invalid.  Their
presumptive validity is not important because if you try to take such
an order to "court" (CFJ alleging contempt) the invalid order defense
can be raised.

